g.text: Each port (A | B) is independent for read/write operations. Each operation is executed in one
clock cycle. In case of reading/writing to the same address, both operations are done in the
same clock. both port A operation has priority over port B.
Since the results of the point adder correspond to the updated value
of the buckets, it will be connected to port A to prioritize write operations.
Note: There's a possibility to use the output_A from the memory mode
for the second loop. For that to happen we would need an arbiter (Or
some mechanism) to decide which component uses the A port first (It
could be the point adder or the common bus)
Note: The memory has a 2 clock delay until the value is available.
